cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.DC 

The paper deals with the transmission of 360 VR video to multiple users, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) and networking (cs.NI) aspects. The optimization problems discussed in the paper involve resource allocation and quality level selection, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses a Difference of Convex (DC) programming problem, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
